20/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The deputy education ministers of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro signed a declaration Saturday (18 October) on the development of lifelong learning.
The document was sealed during a two-day conference in Skopje.
A fair held as part of the conference featured information about government agencies and NGOs that promote and develop adult education in Southeast Europe.
(MIA - 19/10/03)
